 User</span><br>  Posts: 711<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/03 3:43:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my magelo</span><hr size=1> Alrighty <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Your weapon is good and will do great.<br>
If I were to suggest a set of equipment that you might want to try and get..<br>
<br>
Pair of Silver Chitin Armbands or Wristbands or whatever they are called.<br>
<br>
Pair of Deepwater Vambraces, or Crystal Chitin Vambraces.  Chitin gives Stamina, but Deepwater is pretty easy to get hold off.<br>
<br>
Crystal Chitin Boots.  Nice AC, strength.<br>
<br>
Your Fine Antique Ring is good, mana preservation II is always nice.  Keep the resist ring for dragon raids if you ever go on them, and swap it out for a 6/65 ring (the ones you see in the Bazaar, I can't remember the name).  Or, if you can convince a group to go there in a few levels, a Shadel Bandit Ring.  Not as good on the HP, but the mana is worth it.<br>
<br>
Goranga Idol.  Nice upgrade to your range slot, cheap as hell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Keep the topaz earring and swap it out with something with some decent AC/HP when you aren't up against casters.  The other is alright, but you may want to consider the same on that ear.<br>
<br>
Your helm is decent enough, but I would honestly suggest saving up a bit of cash for a Deepwater Helm.  It will make your life ten times easier, and has some great AC on it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
As for haste.<br>
<br>
If you can get an FBSS for your waist slot, grab a pair of Crystal Chitin Gauntlets.  This may be easier as you are of the level where Lower Guk has great experience, and is a lot of fun to hunt in <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
If you can grab a pair of Silver Chitin Handwraps, either go for Axogereths (sp?) Belt of Defense if you have the money or the Maiden's Eye group to do so, or a Chintinous Belt that I will try and get for you next time we're unlucky enough to have to go through a Fungus Grove shard camp.  I believe this is the optimal performance suggestion, but the difference is only a few AC, 1% haste and very few HP.<br>
<br>
Don't worry about your WIS just yet, it's a secondary concern to STA, HP, AC.  You've got 100 and that will do for the time being, just stick to Cease and Stun for aggro holding and it'll serve you great <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
As for food, Halas Meat Pies.  If you're worried about your WIS and you've got money going spare, try and grab a bit of Qeynos Afternoon Tea.<br>
<br>
There is equipment better than I have suggested above, but it is all equipment that you can actually camp, or is easily within the typical price range of your level given a week or two to get money. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakanome>Bakanome</A> at: 4/5/03 3:45:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elsbetsquishytoes>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br>  Posts: 701<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/03 5:49:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my magelo</span><hr size=1> I'd dump Golden Topaz earring posthaste, and your Etched Iron Mask.<br>
<br>
Weapon is very good, and your breastplate is decent.  Hero Bracer is decent, Velium Diamond Wedding Ring is the best item you have.  Skull Shaped Barbute is decent.  Your belt is no good, I suggest an FBSS there.  I don't know much about paladins, but you have a pretty low str/dex/agi, and have zero buffs to your wisdom, and none of this is good.<br>
<br>
Black Alloy Medallion might be nicer in your neck slot than the Amulet of the Grey Wastes.  Very nice stamina buff on that amulet, but its main use is for the EB.<br>
<br>
Elvish paladins have some really nice armor, but I figger you don't have much money, and that's the main roadblock you have.  Either you have to buy or smith this armor, and I don't think you have the means to do either, but all that acrylia should be replaced with racial armor, which is better ( and easier to come by,)  then what you can get from the Old Planes. <br>
<br>
I don't know what else to suggest here, I look at your raw stats and I feel badly for you, your survivability must be very low.  Anything you wear that's chain mail should be replaced.  I think you could find a better back slot item, though what you have now is pretty decent despite the all/all status.  Spend a couple of days hanging around the bazaar.  Find a good buy for like an Orc Fang earring, for starters, and stuff (at least) a Silver Ruby Veil into that face slot instead of the mask you have now.  4 str and 4 wis for very cheap, and I think that serves you better than 6AC and 1 vs. magic.<br>
<br>
I'd probably look for:<br>
Gauntlets of the Black   <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  <br>
AC: +15 Str: +4 Wis: +3<br>
<br>
Those are common, and should be inexpensive.  This is the type of thing you want to look for, is something that's common and provides a long-term value for the cost.  I wore a Forest Loop, Dark Ember, and a Charred Guardian Shield for many seasons of my clericin' career.  I still wear my Velium Ruby veil that I bought in my late 30s ( 8 str, 8 wis ) to this day.  Upgrades to those didn't come until the mid 50s.  That's the type of thing to look for.  Find the cheapest item you can afford that will provide the longest value, and buy it.  I don't have paladinly advice, though.  I can take 1000pp and make a very nice priest, but I can't do the same with a melee, hybrid, or wiggler.  <br>
